I wanted to ask, just for a quick description, the freedom house in Jackson is red on its character.

01:22:16.780 --> 01:22:17.780
Oh.

01:22:17.780 --> 01:22:25.780
It was a unique place, and having grown up in a large family, it was not uncomfortable for me.

01:22:26.780 --> 01:22:37.780
The cast of characters, which included Lawrence Giyat, Cole Ladell, who was from Jackson, and the ten two of them also worked for Medge Evers,

01:22:37.780 --> 01:22:44.780
would come and cook for us, because although I grew up in a large family, I didn't learn to cook.

01:22:44.780 --> 01:22:47.780
I had to take care of the children, the younger children.

01:22:47.780 --> 01:22:48.780
Blackhooked.

01:22:49.780 --> 01:22:55.780
The house was, I think, initially rented by the Freedom Riders.

01:22:55.780 --> 01:23:04.780
It was a big pole, break, pole, and Catherine Brooks, and Diane Nash, James Bevel.

01:23:04.780 --> 01:23:06.780
That's the McKinney.

01:23:06.780 --> 01:23:07.780
That's the McKinney.

01:23:07.780 --> 01:23:17.780
But it was a place that everybody could stand on one roof, and I was looking at some notes that I had come across recently.

01:23:18.780 --> 01:23:26.780
About how we would question each other and talk about strategy, and so forth.

01:23:26.780 --> 01:23:36.780
It was a learning experience, because I was learning, my first experience meeting the Freedom Riders was like,

01:23:37.780 --> 01:23:38.780
Oh my God, what have you been?

01:23:38.780 --> 01:23:39.780
What have you been?

01:23:39.780 --> 01:23:51.780
It was a Masonic Temple upstairs by Megas office, and Tom Hayden, Charles McDue, Mary and Barry, John Lewis,

01:23:51.780 --> 01:24:03.780
Dion Diamond, all these young people were there, and it's like, oh my God, I've been looking for you since I was 14 years old.

01:24:04.780 --> 01:24:21.780
And so they stayed in state to do organizing, and that was the catalyst that we needed in order to continue to work that we had chosen us, all of us had envisioned there in Mississippi.

01:24:21.780 --> 01:24:31.780
And it took them to come in to just break it open, and they had to support the local community, women united, a women power unlimited had organized for the Freedom Riders.

01:24:32.780 --> 01:24:36.780
A lot of advocates there, for the Freedom Riders, from the local community.

01:24:36.780 --> 01:24:57.780
So the network was vast, and once the Freedom Riders came in, that gave the infusion, the power, and every Friday we would go in to do the end of classes, to do community organizing and to learn.

01:24:58.780 --> 01:25:06.780
And that was the first time I remember the Freedom Riders in depth, I remember that seeing them over there, but also remember them on campus.

01:25:06.780 --> 01:25:23.780
We got to Tugulu, the Freedom Riders had come back for their hearing, and it was early September, and I saw all these people, whites, and blacks sitting out on the lawn, and just relaxing, and so on.

01:25:23.780 --> 01:25:32.780
And I remember asking someone I think was roommate, who were those people out there, and she said, oh, those are the Freedom Riders, I said, what?

01:25:32.780 --> 01:25:40.780
And it was extraordinary, because we had wanted to go on the Freedom Riders, and our father, and uncle told us we couldn't do it.

01:25:40.780 --> 01:25:48.780
We had gone to Chicago for the summer to work, but we wanted to join the Freedom Riders, and the reason they told us we couldn't was because it was so dangerous.

01:25:48.780 --> 01:25:54.780
And that was the last time we ever asked anyone if we could do anything, from then on we just went ahead and did it.

01:25:54.780 --> 01:26:02.780
Someone told me that they saw a record where George Russell Moore had put me out of the court.

01:26:02.780 --> 01:26:15.780
I attended a trial with one of Freedom Riders, and one of the police officers was telling so many lies, and I was sitting there looking, and the George kept looking at me, and then finally he said,

01:26:15.780 --> 01:26:25.780
with a young lady in the black dress, get up and leave, and I got up and stuck and threw my head and went on out the door.

01:26:25.780 --> 01:26:33.780
But it's recorded some way, because someone told me that they saw it, but it was one of the Freedom Riders trial.

01:26:33.780 --> 01:26:43.780
If so transparent, the lies were so transparent until just couldn't help but sit in the marble, and I'm one who usually gives them a self-aware by looking.

01:26:43.780 --> 01:26:44.780
Expression?

01:26:44.780 --> 01:26:45.780
Expression, rather severe.

01:26:45.780 --> 01:26:47.780
And someone called him a film set.

01:26:47.780 --> 01:26:51.780
No, someone has written it.

01:26:51.780 --> 01:26:56.780
I was in jail.

01:26:56.780 --> 01:27:09.780
But George Cox, the Federal Fifth Circuit, was so evil. He referred to us as niggas in the courtroom.

01:27:09.780 --> 01:27:20.780
And I had, when I went back to Jackson to the 50th Freedom Riders reunion last summer, I met a young black man who replaced George Cox.

01:27:20.780 --> 01:27:35.780
It was the most amazing thing. I couldn't believe he said, I tell him, I said, when he was introduced at this dinner, and that he was on the fifth circuit, and I went up to him afterwards, and I said,

01:27:35.780 --> 01:27:41.780
I was tried by George Cox, and he said, I replaced him.

01:27:41.780 --> 01:27:42.780
As you got him, he was kidding.

01:27:42.780 --> 01:27:45.780
This is quite injustice in my herd.

01:27:45.780 --> 01:27:47.780
I couldn't believe it.

01:27:47.780 --> 01:27:50.780
It was truly remarkable. 50 years later.

01:27:50.780 --> 01:28:02.780
I'm so looking both to all the work that goes down to Mississippi, that you were right in the middle of, especially Miss Ladner, in voter registration, in the MFDP.

01:28:02.780 --> 01:28:07.780
Maybe we can enter into that, and touch on that. Very, very important work.

